2:T7c4,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Make (Integromat) better than Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It depends on your needs. Make (Integromat) scores 9.0 overall while Power Automate scores 7.0. Make (Integromat) is best for power users and agencies, while Power Automate excels for Microsoft 365 users and enterprises."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which is cheaper, Make (Integromat) or Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Make (Integromat) starts at Free and Power Automate starts at $15/mo. Make (Integromat) offers a free plan.  Overall value depends on which features you need."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I switch from Make (Integromat) to Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, most users can migrate between these platforms. Both Make (Integromat) and Power Automate support data import/export. The migration process typically involves exporting your data from one platform and importing it into the other. Some tools also offer migration assistance to make the transition smoother."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What do users say about Make (Integromat) vs Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"On review platforms, Make (Integromat) holds an overall rating of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10. Power Automate has an overall rating of 7/10 and ease of use score of 6/10. Users praise Make (Integromat) for superior visual workflow builder and Power Automate for deep microsoft ecosystem integration."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which should I choose in 2026, Make (Integromat) or Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In 2026, we recommend Make (Integromat) for most users based on its overall score and feature set. However, Power Automate remains a strong contender, especially if you prioritize deep microsoft ecosystem integration. Try both free trials before committing."}}]}0:{"b